# UV Workspace Monorepo

Use this reference when the user wants a monorepo with multiple packages, such as `backend`, `frontend`, several independent packages, or several independent APIs/Apps.

## Typical layout

```text
repo/
  pyproject.toml
  backend/
    pyproject.toml
    src/backend/
  frontend/
    pyproject.toml
    src/frontend/
```

## Root pyproject.toml

```toml
[tool.uv.workspace]
members = ["backend", "frontend"]

[tool.uv.sources]
backend = { workspace = true }
frontend = { workspace = true }
```

## Notes
- Ask the user abotu their package structure and needs before addings workspace members, unless it is already clear.
- Add only the workspace members the user actually needs. Ask about requirements if not specified by the user.
- Start simple; split further only when there is a clear boundary.
- uv workspaces don't work well with different programming languages, such as Python backend and JavaScript frontend. In that case, suggest a vscode workspace instead.